  "script": "The biggest rocket ever? SpaceX's Starship stands 120 meters tall, towering over the Statue of Liberty. Its Super Heavy booster lights 33 Raptor engines at once, with twice the thrust of the Saturn 5 moon rocket. The whole ship is stainless steel, the same metal as your kitchen sink. After separation, the booster flies itself back to the launch tower, where 2 giant steel arms catch it in midair. Every catch saves SpaceX millions, because the booster flies again instead of sinking into the Gulf. Elon Musk says the endgame is Mars, a city of 1 million people on the red planet. NASA already booked Starship to land its next astronauts on the Moon. So, would YOU ride it to Mars?",
